[size=120][b]General options[/b][/size]
[list][*] [b]Drag&Drop capabilities:[/b] If enabled, Custom Buttons buttons can be installed by simply drag and dropping a Custom Buttons URL or a CB XML file into any toolbar.
[*] [b]Drag&Drop - Require Control key:[/b] If enabled, the Control key must be pressed for the drag operation to attempt to install a button. [b]Note:[/b] It's recommended to at least enable one modifier key.
[*] [b]Drag&Drop - Require Alt key:[/b] If enabled, the Alt key must be pressed for the drag operation to attempt to install a button. [b]Note:[/b] It's recommended to at least enable one modifier key.
[*] [b]Hide 'Customize...' menu item from CB context:[/b] Hide [i]'Customize...'[/i] menu item from CB context.
[*] [b]Invert dark icons colours:[/b] Most of the icons used by this button are dark/black. With this option enabled, a white filter is applied to those icons to make them visible on dark themes.
[*] [b]Show ID on exported buttons:[/b] If enabled, it will add the number ID to the XML file name of exported button.
[*] [b]Show move alert:[/b] If enabled, a dialog with instructions will appear every time a button is selected to be moved.
[*] [b]Show 'Remove to palette' alert:[/b] If enabled, a dialog will appear every time a button is removed to the application palette.
[*] [b]Set custom export path:[/b] Set a custom path location to store exported XML buttons.
[*] [b]Clear last used path:[/b] Every time any import option is used, the last opened location is stored. This option clears that last used folder and resets it to the default export location.[/list]

